Julius Mndawe, the so-called Masoyi Monster, made headlines when he was arrested for the rape and murder of five young women between the ages of 15 and 24. He took police to his home in Masoyi where he pointed out the bodies. Slindelo Masikane returned to the area and spoke to some of the grieving families. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - He must rot in jail. That's the sentiment of the families whose loved ones were found buried in the yard of the man dubbed the Masoyi Monster. Serial killer Julius Mndawe has been sentenced to five life terms plus 25 years imprisonment. Mndawe was arrested in July 2019 following the disappearance of several young women in the area. Investigations led police to his home. Mndawe confessed to killing 15-year-old Banele Khoza, 17-year-old Noxolo Mdluli, 17-year-old Felicia Ndlovu, 19-year-old Nomthandazo Mdluli and 24-year-old Tokkie Tlaka. * eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports.